Hi my ads got rejected and the message says "Your ad appears to mimic a real site to promote your product or services, which is in violation of our Advertising Policy. Please update your landing page to a proper page with substantiated claims." It's my business I'm running the ads for. My landing page is hosted on my gohighlevel account

Hi there! It sounds like your ad was rejected because the landing page appears to mimic a real site, which is against our Advertising Policy. To resolve this, you should update your landing page to ensure it clearly represents your business and includes substantiated claims. For more details on why ads get rejected and how to fix them, you can check out this article: [My ad got rejected. What's next?](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18085960681101-My-ad-got-rejected-What-s-next). If you need further assistance, feel free to reach out!
